# .envrc.local — per-worktree environment overrides
#
# In the default workflow you do NOT need this file. `mise run dev` (and
# `dev:ensure-ports`) automatically picks random free ports on first run and
# writes them to .dev/ports.env (gitignored). All dev tasks and the agents:*
# harness source that file automatically.
#
# Only create .envrc.local if you need to OVERRIDE the auto-assigned ports —
# for example, to keep a fixed port that another tool expects.
#
# HOW TO USE (direnv)
# Add the following to your repo-root .envrc:
#   [ -f .envrc.local ] && source_env .envrc.local
# Then run: direnv allow
#
# HOW TO USE (without direnv)
# Source manually before running dev:
#   source .envrc.local && mise run dev
#
# VARIABLE REFERENCE
# ------------------
#   PORT              API server port (Elysia reads this)
#   E2E_WEB_PORT      Vite dev server port (vite.config.ts reads E2E_WEB_PORT first, then PORT)
#   POSTGRES_PORT     Host-side Postgres port (mapped into the Docker container)
#   DATABASE_URL      Full Postgres connection string
#   DATABASE_DIRECT_URL  Direct URL for Drizzle migrations (usually same as DATABASE_URL)
#   COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME  Docker Compose project name (scopes container/network names)
#   NBR_API_URL       Local nbr API URL (forwarded into agents by the plugin hooks)
#
# EXAMPLE (custom fixed ports — pick values that don't collide on your machine)
# export COMPOSE_PROJECT_NAME="nearest-neighbor-feat-my-feature"
# export PORT=17247
# export E2E_WEB_PORT=19247
# export POSTGRES_PORT=15447
# export DATABASE_URL="postgres://nearest-neighbor:nearest-neighbor@localhost:15447/nearest-neighbor"
# export DATABASE_DIRECT_URL="postgres://nearest-neighbor:nearest-neighbor@localhost:15447/nearest-neighbor"
# export NBR_API_URL="http://localhost:17247"
